## Gate: PRD Validation (6-Point Rubric)

**Purpose**: Ensure all PRDs maintain consistent quality standards.

**When Applied**: Before any PRD transitions from Drafting to Actionable status.

### The Iron Law

**NO PRD BECOMES ACTIONABLE WITHOUT PASSING ALL 6 RUBRIC CHECKS**

If a PRD fails any criterion, it must be:
1. Refined until it passes, OR
2. Demoted to a ticket (if too small for a PRD), OR
3. Split into multiple PRDs (if too large for one quarter), OR
4. Kept in Drafting status (if information is pending)

### The 6 Criteria

#### 1. Objectives Clear
PRD has a well-defined customer statement with problem and desired outcome.

| Pass ‚úì | Fail ‚úó |
|--------|--------|
| Complete "I am / I'm trying to / But / Because / Which makes me feel" | Only vague problem statement |
| Specific customer description with motivations | "Users need this feature" |
| Clear desired outcome articulated | Missing success criteria |

#### 2. Use Cases Defined
PRD has explicit in-scope use cases with descriptions.

| Pass ‚úì | Fail ‚úó |
|--------|--------|
| 2+ specific use cases documented | No use cases listed |
| Each use case has a description | Only bullet points without context |
| Out-of-scope items explicitly stated | "Out of scope: TBD" |

#### 3. Requirements Structured
PRD has requirements organized by milestone with priority levels.

| Pass ‚úì | Fail ‚úó |
|--------|--------|
| Requirements grouped by milestone | Flat list of requirements |
| Each requirement has P0/P1/P2 priority | No prioritization |
| Acceptance criteria defined | Vague or missing acceptance criteria |
| User story format used | Just feature descriptions |

#### 4. Timeline Present
PRD has milestones with expected delivery timeline.

| Pass ‚úì | Fail ‚úó |
|--------|--------|
| Milestones table populated | No timeline section |
| Expected delivery dates/quarters | "Timeline: TBD" |
| Teams assigned to milestones | No ownership identified |

#### 5. Success Measurable
PRD has success metrics and/or opportunity sizing.

| Pass ‚úì | Fail ‚úó |
|--------|--------|
| Specific metrics identified | "We'll know it when we see it" |
| Signals for success defined | No measurement plan |
| Opportunity sizing included (if applicable) | Impact not quantified |

#### 6. DACE Assigned
PRD has Driver, Approver, and key Contributors identified.

| Pass ‚úì | Fail ‚úó |
|--------|--------|
| Driver clearly identified | "Driver: TBD" |
| Approver assigned | No approval authority |
| At least one driving team with roles | No team ownership |
| Escalation path defined | No escalation plan |

